      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TERRY KEEPING (2) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his head turning win the start prior, getting around Gawler over 400m in 22.52. Rates a top chance if runs up to time two back. HERE COMES RHEA (1) took the sit on the lead from an outside box but levelled up and drew clear to score (31.63) at Angle Park in a Grade 6 over 530m. Has good speed and is aided by the cherry draw. Sure to be thereabouts. INVICTUS TOMMY (5) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 1.3 lengths second (17.08) in a Grade 6 at Murray Bridge Straight. The form from his last run stacks up well. Likely to be in the finish again. ELLSWORTH (7) is worth including after a top-three finish most recently.",
